{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"baf0168c-993f-4cfb-bf50-b566e06de653","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nHot reload for the testing platform works when the test project is executed directly as an executable. With `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` enabled and the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package installed, you run:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run -- --hotreload\n```\n\nThis launches the test host in hot-reload mode, watching for file changes and re-running affected tests automatically. `dotnet test` does not support the `--hotreload` flag and won't activate the hot-reload pipeline.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"905ff648-e427-43bd-9ed9-8b0e1dfb2f75","outputTokens":135,"requestId":"B458:2EE1E2:E5B54A:F3A37A:6A044D5D"},"id":"ca3228f1-ee9b-4e9a-bec2-893756bccfa9","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:07:32.408Z","parentId":"1326982c-af6f-4197-bb66-5eefa0ce0c29"}
